public class StringRangeConstraint
extends RangeConstraint<String,String>

A default range constraint for String form elements. The Collator functionality will be used for comparison.

Since:
2.0
Author:
Martti Tamm (martti@araneaframework.org)

Constructor Detail

StringRangeConstraint

public StringRangeConstraint(FormElement<String,String> fieldLo,
                             FormElement<String,String> fieldHi,
                             boolean allowEquals)
Creates a new string range constraint that checks that form field values are in the right order: the fieldLo is less than fieldHi. It is possible to specify through allowEquals whether the values may be equal or not.

Parameters:
fieldLo - The value of this field is checked to be less than the value of fieldHi (or null)
fieldHi - The value of this field is checked to be greater than the value of fieldLo (or null)
allowEquals - If this is true, the constraint will be considered satisfied when values of fieldLo and fieldHi are equal. Otherwise the constraint won't be satisfied in this case.

Creates a new string range constraint that checks that form field values are in the right order: the fieldLo is less than fieldHi. It is possible to specify through allowEquals whether the values may be equal or not.

Parameters:
fieldLo - The value of this field is checked to be less than the value of fieldHi (or null)
fieldHi - The value of this field is checked to be greater than the value of fieldLo (or null)
allowEquals - If this is true, the constraint will be considered satisfied when values of fieldLo and fieldHi are equal. Otherwise the constraint won't be satisfied in this case.
locale - The locale to use for comparing strings. Defaults to the current application locale, when null.

StringRangeConstraint

public StringRangeConstraint(FormElement<String,String> fieldLo,
                             FormElement<String,String> fieldHi,
                             boolean allowEquals,
                             Locale locale,
                             int decomposition,
                             int strength)
Creates a new string range constraint that checks that form field values are in the right order: the fieldLo is less than fieldHi. It is possible to specify through allowEquals whether the values may be equal or not.

Parameters:
fieldLo - The value of this field is checked to be less than the value of fieldHi (or null)
fieldHi - The value of this field is checked to be greater than the value of fieldLo (or null)
allowEquals - If this is true, the constraint will be considered satisfied when values of fieldLo and fieldHi are equal. Otherwise the constraint won't be satisfied in this case.
locale - The locale to use for comparing strings. Defaults to the current application locale, when null.
decomposition - The decomposition type used when comparing Strings. See Collator.getDecomposition() for more information.
strength - The minimum level of difference considered significant during comparison. See Collator.setStrength(int) for more information.
See Also:
Collator
